              <p>&ldquo;It was a wonderful experience to be involved and have the opportunity to represent the town of Warren,&rdquo; he adds. &ldquo;I got to meet and work with the chefs who make the New Jersey food scene what it is. This was really an honor, and a weekend I won&rsquo;t forget.&rdquo;</p>
            <p><strong>&nbsp;Warren residents know the Gramaglia name means outstanding food.</strong></p>
            <p>For more than seven years, Saly Gs has greeted guests looking for a unique, top-flight dining experience in the Pheasant Run Shopping Center. &ldquo;Fine dining, white tablecloths, and an absolute commitment to customer satisfaction,&rdquo; is how he described it in an interview for<strong> The</strong> <strong>Showcase Magazine</strong> last year. The restaurant has been an Open Table Diners&rsquo; Choice Winner, and carries on the Gramaglia family tradition of amazing food in welcoming, family-style atmospheres.</p>
            <p>Joe learned to cook the old-fashioned way &ndash; from his Italian mother and father. He studied cookbooks and absorbed as much as he could from watching cooking shows on TV, but the firsthand experience alongside his parents ultimately molded him into the professional he is today.</p>
            <p><strong>The Showcase Magazine</strong> congratulates Joe on his outstanding performance at this prestigious New Jersey event!</p>
          
